bit.name: PmcStrap0_CPUPWRGDStretchingWDTimerEnabled
bit.label: CPUPWRGD Stretching WD Timer Enabled
bit.ui_params: {'read_only': 'false', 'description':'The WD Timer is enabled by setting this strap to \'0\'. Timer runs while all of the following conditions are satisfied: SLP_S3# = 1, PCH_PWROK = 1, CPUPWRGD = 0. Typically, the timer stops once CPUPWRGD asserts.'}
bit.params: {'value_list':{'CPUPWRGD Stretching watchdog timer is enabled':'0x0','CPUPWRGD Stretching watchdog timer is disabled':'0x1'} }

bit.name: PmcStrap0_SYS_PWROKSyncPoint
bit.label: SYS_PWROK Sync Point
bit.ui_params: {'read_only': 'false', 'description':'Select whether SYS_PWROK is required prior to CPUPWRGD high or SUS_STAT# high.'}
bit.params: {'value_list':{'Wait for SYS_PWROK before driving CPUPWRGD high':'0x0','Wait for SYS_PWROK before driving SUS_STAT# high':'0x1'} }

bit.name: PmcStrap0_StartMonitoringTHRMTRIPValidPoint

bit.params: {'value_list':{'Start monitoring THRMTRIP# at PLTRST# deassertion':'0x0','Start monitoring THRMTRIP# at CPUPWRGD assertion':'0x1'} }

bit.name: PmcStrap0_IOE_RST_SYNC_EN

bit.name: PmcStrap0_t573Timing

bit.ui_params: {'read_only': 'false', 'description':'t573 is the min timing from XCK_PLL locked to CPUPWRGD high'}

bit.name: PmcStrap0_t1001Timing
bit.label: t1001 Timing
bit.ui_params:
{'read_only': 'false', 'description':'t1001 is the min timing from either CPUPWRGD or SYS_PWROK(Depend on SYS_PWROK Sync point strap setting) assertion to SUS_STAT# deassertion

SYS_PWROK Sync point strap setting and start point logic as below:
STRAP119 Bit [2]:
1 = SYS_PWROK
0 = CPUPWRGD'}

bit.name: PmcStrap0_APWROKTiming
